    "Psychoanalysts and psychotherapists applying different approaches have proposed the scientific and professional independence of psychotherapy ever since the socalled question of lay analysis appeared in the 1920s (Pritz, 1996).",
    "Following the radical-constructivistic method called treatmentpossibilities-expanding psychotherapy science, there have been nearly as many psychotherapy approaches as there are psychotherapists (Raile, 2024).",
